  "prompt": "I am very concerned about my future. I couldn\u2019t clear my JEE exam, I worked hard, I feel demotivated, how do I believe in myself?",
  "response": "I understand that not clearing the JEE exam can be extremely disappointing, especially after working hard. Here are some supportive suggestions:\n\n1. Emotional Support\n\u2022 It's okay to feel disappointed\n\u2022 Your worth isn't defined by a single exam result\n\u2022 Many successful people have faced similar setbacks\n\n2. Alternative Paths\n\u2022 Consider other engineering entrance exams\n\u2022 Explore diploma courses\n\u2022 Look into private engineering colleges\n\u2022 Consider lateral entry options\n\n3. Personal Development\n\u2022 Analyze your preparation strategy\n\u2022 Identify areas of improvement\n\u2022 Consider professional coaching\n\u2022 Take mock tests to build confidence\n\n4. Positive Mindset\n\u2022 Remember this is one moment, not your entire life\n\u2022 Success has multiple definitions\n\u2022 Stay persistent and motivated\n\u2022 Learn from this experience\n\n5. Practical Steps\n\u2022 Discuss options with career counselors\n\u2022 Talk to parents/mentors\n\u2022 Explore different streams\n\u2022 Consider work experience or skill development\n\n6. Mental Health\n\u2022 Don't be too hard on yourself\n\u2022 Practice self-care\n\u2022 Talk to friends/family\n\u2022 Consider professional counseling if needed\n\nRemember:\n\u2022 One exam doesn't determine your potential\n\u2022 Your determination matters more than results\n\u2022 Stay positive and keep moving forward\n\nWould you like to discuss your specific situation in more detail?",
